      "content": "exactly. it’s not just \"theoretical\" interest for me. i’ve seen the discrepancies. when you look at the packet headers and the way the latency fluctuates in sync with certain high-net-worth movements, it's like the actual money is being \"represented\" by the way the data is structured. it's almost as if the metadata is the actual ledger, and the transaction amounts we see on the surface are just decoys to keep the public from noticing how much is actually moving. how would someone even begin to quantify a currency that only exists in that layer of the architecture?",
